        "answer": "A **progressive tax** system imposes a higher tax rate as an individual’s income increases. This means wealthier individuals pay a larger percentage of their income in taxes. Examples include the U.S. federal income tax and estate tax.\n\nA **regressive tax** system imposes a higher relative burden on lower-income individuals, as the tax rate effectively decreases as income rises. This occurs because the tax is the same for everyone, regardless of income. Examples include sales tax and excise taxes.\n\nThe key difference lies in how the tax burden changes relative to income: progressive taxes increase with income, while regressive taxes decrease in relative burden as income rises.",
