        "question": "What is the penalty tax for failing to take a Required Minimum Distribution (RMD)?",
        "answer": "If an account holder fails to take the full Required Minimum Distribution (RMD) from a qualified retirement plan or IRA by the applicable deadline, a penalty tax may apply.\n\nThe penalty is **25%** of the amount that was required but not withdrawn.\n\nHowever, if the mistake is corrected in a timely manner, the penalty may be reduced to **10%**.\n\nThe IRS considers the correction timely if the shortfall is withdrawn and Form 5329 is filed within **two years** from the end of the year in which the RMD should have been taken.\n\nThis excise tax is reported and paid using **IRS Form 5329**.\n\nTo avoid the penalty, account holders should ensure that RMDs begin by April 1 of the year after they turn **73** (for those turning 73 after 2022, based on SECURE Act 2.0), and annually by December 31 thereafter.",
