        "question": "What does Section 404 of ERISA require of fiduciaries?",
        "answer": "Section 404 of the Employee Retirement Income Security Act (ERISA) outlines the core fiduciary duties for those managing retirement plan assets.\n\nUnder Section 404, fiduciaries must:\n\n- Act **solely in the interest of plan participants and beneficiaries**.\n\n- Carry out their duties with the **care, skill, prudence, and diligence** of a prudent person familiar with such matters.\n\n- Diversify plan investments to **minimize the risk of large losses**.\n\n- Follow the **plan documents** (to the extent they are consistent with ERISA).\n\nThis is often referred to as the **prudent person rule**, and it establishes the legal standard of conduct for fiduciaries. Failure to comply may result in personal liability for any losses to the plan.",
