        "question": "What is an Investment Policy Statement (IPS)?",
        "answer": "An Investment Policy Statement (IPS) is a written document that outlines the investment goals, strategies, and guidelines for managing a portfolio, typically for a retirement plan or institutional investor.\n\nKey components of an IPS include:\n\n- The plan’s **investment objectives** (e.g., growth, income, preservation of capital)\n\n- **Time horizon**, **risk tolerance**, and **return expectations**\n\n- **Asset allocation targets** and permitted asset classes\n\n- Criteria for **selecting and monitoring investments**\n\n- Responsibilities of fiduciaries, investment managers, and service providers\n\n- **Rebalancing guidelines** and procedures\n\n- Any specific **restrictions** (e.g., no tobacco stocks, ESG criteria)\n\nWhile not required under ERISA, an IPS is a critical best practice for fiduciaries. It helps demonstrate that investment decisions are made prudently and consistently, and it serves as a benchmark to evaluate performance and fiduciary compliance.",
