        "answer": "A Summary Plan Description (SPD) is a document required by ERISA that explains the key features of an employer-sponsored retirement or health benefit plan in plain language.\n\nThe SPD must be provided to all plan participants and beneficiaries and must include:\n\n- The plan’s name, administrator, and sponsor\n\n- Eligibility requirements and participation rules\n\n- Description of plan benefits and how they are calculated\n\n- Vesting schedules\n\n- Procedures for claiming benefits\n\n- Circumstances that may result in loss of benefits\n\n- Participants' rights under ERISA\n\nThe SPD must be distributed to participants within 90 days of becoming covered by the plan or within 120 days of a new plan being established. It must be updated every 10 years (or every 5 years if there are material changes).\n\nIt serves as the primary communication tool for ensuring participants understand their rights and benefits under the plan.",
