        "answer": "The time value of money means that a dollar today is worth more than a dollar in the future because you can invest it and earn interest.\n\nMoney now has the potential to grow over time. For example, if you have $100 today and earn 5% interest, you’ll have $105 in a year. But if you wait a year to receive the $100, you miss out on that extra $5.\n\nThis concept helps people compare options when deciding how and when to use their money."
