        "question": "What are the rules concerning outside business activities?",
        "answer": "FINRA Rule 3270 requires registered representatives to provide prior written notice to their firm before engaging in any outside business activity (OBA), including compensated and uncompensated roles. The firm must review the activity to determine if it conflicts with the rep’s duties. While firm approval is not always required, they must supervise if the activity is securities-related. Failure to disclose OBAs can result in disciplinary action."
